The paper proposes a new multi-objective contextual multi-armed bandit problem and algorithm, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper discusses the algorithm's performance in synthetic and real-world datasets, which further supports its relevance to these categories.
